==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Editorial
<hw>Ed`i*to"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to an editor; written or sanctioned by an editor; <as>as,
<ex>editorial</ex> labors; <ex>editorial</ex> remarks.</as></def> <--
<col><b>editorial content</b></col> -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Editorial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Editorial
<hw>Ed`i*to"ri*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A leading article in a
newspaper or magazine; an editorial article; an article published as an
expression of the views of the editor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>editorialize</ent>⟦br⟧
